Here's the explanation of each column from your E-Commerce Dataset:

CUSTOMER ID: Unique identifier for each customer.

TENURE: Number of years or months the customer has been associated with the platform.

PREFERRED LOGIN DEVICE: The device most often used by the customer to log in (e.g., Phone, Mobile Phone, Computer).

CITY TIER: Indicates the customer's city classification — Tier 1, 2, or 3 based on infrastructure and development.

WAREHOUSE TO HOME: Distance (probably in km) from the warehouse to the customer's home.

PREFERRED PAYNENT MODE: The customer’s most used payment method (e.g., Debit Card, Credit Card, UPI).

GENDER: Gender of the customer (Male/Female).

HOURS SPEND ON APP: Average number of hours the customer spends on the app.

NUMBER OF DEVICE REGISTERED: How many devices the customer has registered with the platform.

PREFERED ORDER CAT: The most frequently ordered product category (e.g., Mobile, Laptop & Accessory).

SATISFACTION SCORE: Customer satisfaction level, usually on a scale of 1–5.

MARITAL STATUS: Marital status of the customer (e.g., Single, Married).

NUMBER OF ADDRESS: Number of delivery addresses associated with the customer.

COMPLAIN: Whether the customer has lodged any complaints (1 = Yes, 0 = No).

ORDER AMOUNT HIKE FROM LAST YEAR: Percentage increase in total order amount compared to last year.

COUPON USED: Whether the customer used a coupon (1 = Yes, 0 = No).

ORDER COUNT: Total number of orders placed by the customer.

DAY SINCE LAST ORDER: Days since the last order was placed.

CASH BACK AMOUNT: Cashback earned by the customer (in currency units).

CHURN: Target variable — whether the customer has churned (1 = Yes, 0 = No).
